Session is the sole gateway for reads and writes to files under .drift/. Begin acquires an exclusive advisory lock on .drift/state.lock (creating the file if needed) using flock on Unix and LockFileEx on Windows; it blocks until the lock is acquired and auto-releases on process exit. Close releases the lock and is idempotent. There is no public Lock() method: callers must route all .drift/ I/O through a Session begun at the transaction boundary (typically the lifetime of a single CLI invocation). Concurrent Begin calls from different processes serialize; concurrent Begin calls within the same process block on each other (flock is not reentrant across separate file descriptors of the same file). See pinstore.load and pinstore.save for the transactional callers.